OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 10 Jul to Sun 19 Jul
OL,6,FNorthern and western parts may be
OL,7,Funsettled at first with heavy rain or
OL,8,Fthundery showers, before high pressure
OL,9,Fbecomes reestablished. This will
OL,10,Fcontinue to bring dry and very warm
OL,11,Fweather across England and Wales, but
OL,12,Falways with an ongoing chance of
OL,13,Fthunderstorms moving in from France.
OL,14,FHigh pressure will likely amplify
OL,15,Fnorthwards to bring periods of drier
OL,16,Fand warmer weather to most of Scotland
OL,17,Fand Northern Ireland too. Winds will
OL,18,Fbe light to moderate for most, but
OL,19,Fgusty around any thunderstorms.
OL,20,FTemperatures by day will be widely
OL,21,Fvery warm, hot or even very hot in
OL,22,Fparts of the south. There are signs
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Ffor the heatwave to ease back to more
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fnormal summer temperatures through the
OL,25,Fnext week commencing Monday 13 July.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
